Jeanette Chabalala, News24iStock Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Bloemfontein &ndash; A man has been arrested in connection with the abduction and gang-rape of a 14-year-old Free State girl, police said on Thursday. The 35-year-old man, believed to be from Gauteng, was arrested after Harrismith residents identified him, Sergeant Mmako Mophiring said. He would appear in the Harrismith Magistrate&rsquo;s Court on Friday. Three other suspects were still at large. The girl was forced into a bakkie and blindfolded while on her way to school on Monday. She was raped in the moving bakkie and taken to a house where three other men raped her. Afterwards, a woman who was in the house, instructed her to take a bath.In a separate incident, four men in a blue Toyota bakkie allegedly abducted a 15-year-old girl on her way home from a filling station in QwaQwa on Sunday night. She was taken to a house where she was forced to take tablets, raped and held overnight. Her attackers instructed her to take a bath. She was left on the streets on Monday morning.Last week, six men were arrested after they allegedly raped two girls and left them at a hiking spot in Bloemfontein in February. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.